    Scope and Contents
BLACK COMMUNITY PROJECT 
Hale, long-time resident of the Springfield area, discusses her experiences as a member of the city's African American community. She recalls her family history, farm life and growing up in a  rural area, Springfield neighborhoods and schools, relations with white neighbors, marriage and family life, her husband's work in the Tuxhorn coal mine, the 1908 Springfield race riot, and racial discrimination. 1 tape, 90 mins., 33 pp. 
Interview by Reverend Negil L. McPherson, 1974 
